          "text": "The architecture already has the right boundary; the missing decision is where provider capability ends and llame’s durable transcript begins.\n\n```text\n                 configuration\n                         │\n                 provider connection\n           ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐\n           │                           │\n OpenAI Responses                compatible Chat API\n reasoning summaries             best-effort native reasoning\n           │                           │\n           └────────── normalized ModelClient ──────────┐\n                                                         │\nAI SDK chunks ──> ordered run_events ──> ordered message.parts\n                                                         │\n                                      replay stream / history fetch\n                                                         │\n                                             same UI renderer\n```\n\nCurrent integration points:\n\n| Layer | Existing seam | Needed change |\n|---|---|---|\n| Provider config | `ProviderConfig.type = 'openai'` | It currently conflates native OpenAI and OpenAI-compatible Chat Completions. Add an explicit transport/capability mode. |\n| Model config | `model.reasoning?: boolean` | This is display metadata, not an executable guarantee. Replace/augment with a precise reasoning-output policy. |\n| Model client | `onReasoningDelta(text)` | Preserve provider metadata and normalize *provider-authorized* reasoning output. |\n| Run executor | `reasoning.delta` durable events | Keep it. Change accumulation from a single string to an ordered part collector. |\n| Message persistence | `messages.parts` JSONB | Persist the same ordered reasoning/text/tool sequence that live replay renders. |\n| UI | `MessageReasoning` | Correct integration already exists; change label/default-collapse/duration later, after semantics are correct. |\n\nThe key design fork is configuration:\n\n```yaml\nproviders:\n  - id: openai\n    type: openai\n    transport: responses # native OpenAI, enables reasoning summaries\n    key: \"{env:OPENAI_API_KEY}\"\n\n  - id: local\n    type: openai\n    transport: chat-completions # OpenAI-compatible endpoint\n    baseUrl: \"http://ollama:11434/v1\"\n    key: null\n\nmodels:\n  - id: system:openai:gpt-5\n    provider: openai\n    providerModelId: gpt-5\n    reasoningOutput: summary-auto\n\n  - id: system:local:qwen\n    provider: local\n    providerModelId: qwen3\n    reasoningOutput: if-provided\n```\n\nI would not make `reasoningOutput` a user request parameter. It is operator/model policy: it affects cost, retention, exposure, and provider compatibility. The UI can offer a per-user display preference—collapsed, expanded, hidden—but it should not control what the provider emits or what the system stores.\n\nThe reason OpenAI needs a distinct transport is structural, not cosmetic:\n\n- `openai.chat(...)` was chosen to support OpenRouter, Groq, Ollama, etc.\n- documented OpenAI reasoning summaries are a Responses API feature and require `providerOptions.openai.reasoningSummary`.\n- silently changing all existing `type: openai` models to Responses would break compatible endpoints.\n\nSo the minimal honest scope is:\n\n1. Add a native OpenAI Responses route, opt-in by provider configuration.\n2. Request `reasoningSummary: 'auto'` only for models configured to collect it.\n3. Normalize the resulting chunks into llame’s existing event stream.\n4. Preserve exact part ordering in `messages.parts`.\n5. Keep reasoning excluded from context, compaction, search, and public shares.\n\nThe ordered persistence issue is the real correctness condition:\n\n```text\nLive today:\n  reasoning A → text A → tool X → reasoning B → text B\n\nReload today:\n  reasoning A+B → tool X → text A+B      # incorrect transcript\n\nRequired reload:\n  reasoning A → text A → tool X → reasoning B → text B\n```\n\nThe collector should therefore emit finalized parts at modality boundaries—not concatenate `reasoningText`, `toolParts`, and final `text` at completion. Run events remain the live/reconnect source of truth; `messages.parts` becomes the immutable final projection. OpenCode follows this stronger pattern: lifecycle events accumulate fragments, then persist completed reasoning parts with provider metadata.\n\nTwo policy decisions are still genuinely open before a proposal:\n\n1. **Retention:** keep provider reasoning summaries indefinitely in the private chat, or use a separate retention window / delete control? The current 24k cap is a blunt storage bound, not a product policy.\n2. **Scope:** OpenAI Responses only first, or also normalize tag-based local-model `<think>` output through AI SDK middleware? The latter is broader but substantially less trustworthy and much noisier.\n\nMy recommendation: private retention with an explicit future deletion setting; OpenAI Responses summaries first; preserve the generic normalization seam for Anthropic/local follow-ups. Anything wider combines provider adaptation, data-retention policy, and UI behavior into one diff—the usual way an apparently small feature becomes unreviewable.",
